- !<ScriptComponent/0147ca01-978e-46d6-b0ae-ac86b504f3d4>
  PrefabRemaps:
    []
  Name: CardQueryVoiceAgent
  Enabled: true
  ScriptAsset: !<reference> 5238106c-5e3e-4b44-9b5e-27195870dc2b
  ScriptInputsDefault:
    autoStart: true
    model: true
    enableLogging: true
  ScriptTypesDefault:
    {}
  ScriptInputs:
    "":
      websocketRequirementsObj: !<reference.SceneObject> 9e699c2a-7957-4e80-7e3d-d6c8eccec7dc
      dynamicAudioOutput: !<MappingBased.AssignableType> 4bacfcbc-822f-4c9f-5a6b-440dc7616841
      microphoneRecorder: !<MappingBased.AssignableType_1> 435a158d-ddca-4b73-55b3-c177f477f1b5
      cardDeck: !<MappingBased.AssignableType_2> c99be548-d91a-4909-b4fb-8e0e02d53858
      globeController: !<MappingBased.AssignableType_3> 05388fb0-0dde-44c7-a8c9-1f6a6bb35ced
      autoStart: true
      voice: Leda
      persona: |-
        You are Momo. You help the user find AR trivia cards floating in a deck above a globe. When they describe what they want, call query_cards with the location, topic, date range, and/or keyword you extract, and say a short warm line like 'Gotcha — finding those now!'. If query_cards returns zero cards, ask ONE short clarifying question; if the next try still finds nothing, If the user asks for a location, and the location is not one that is Tokyo, Seattle, or Los Angeles, or a place nearby, tell the user something in effect of :there are no cards in the place they asked for. Note: Long Beach, or AWE (conference) are all equal to Los Angeles.
        DROP your least-certain keyword and query again, briefly narrating each step so the user follows along. When it returns cards, summarize how many and where (e.g. 'I found 3 cards captured in Tokyo!'). If some matches can't be shown (unshown > 0), mention that. After results, the user may ask about the card they're looking at — I will tell you which card thatis; do NOT bring it up or speak about it until they actually ask. Keep replies to one to three warm sentences. To start over or undo, call clear_query.
      model: gemini-live-2.5-flash
      enableLogging: true
  ScriptTypes:
    "":
      {}
